thank you, Artyom, and hope to see you someday :)

Artyom and his sweet girlfriend came to visit us for two nights. They were very gentle, brought original sweets from their homecountry, were interested and nice. Also Artyom read a german goodnight-book to our five-year-old :-) Thank you very much for your kind way of being! Julian and Birgit
He is a nice and smart guy. I talked a lot whit him and he was cooking Dinner for us.

Artyom is a happy and polite guy. We went together climbing, which he never did before.  Played some boardgames and had a great evening in a chinese restaurant with some friends :) I wish him all the best for his last days in Germany.

My boyfriend and I hosted Artyom for one night and it was a great experience! Artyom stayed in my flat tow days , he was really polite and really good guest . And has a lot to share about the culture in his country , I would see you again here or in Belarus :)

text:
I enjoyed my stay with Dmitry, despite lack of time for more thought-provoking conversations in IT world where he is obviously a thought leader and aspiring professional, his ability to describe the situation, matter anything that one could think of is an admirable quality.

Not to mention his skills of cooking and natural hospitality make him memorable host, truly thankful for welcoming me and looking forward to keeping in touch.

Aloha,
A

Dmitry and Oksana were very gracious hosts. They received me in the evening and saved a couple bowls of delicious soup to relieve me from the bitter cold motorcycle drive to Minsk from Brest. They live in a cozy flat on the outskirts of town and Dmitry was nice enough to look into buying my motorcycle from me, which would have been awesome and convenient had it been possible. We had a fun morning starting up my motorcycle which had a dirty spark plug and he gave me several push starts to get it running before I got it fixed up at a mechanic later that day. An incredible duo, the two made my stay in Belarus worth remembering.
I stayed with Dima 3 or 4 years ago. Dima is an excellent host. With him you can talk about travel and hitchhiking. With his family I felt sameself at home. I am glad to get to know them.

I'm very glad to get acquainted with Dima. He is very friendly and knowledgeable. The time spent in Minsk was wonderful. Thank you for the warm welcome and excursion. I wish good luck and all the best.

I have many friends with Dmitry, we've known each other for several years. But only now we have met, my positive expectations were justified one hundred percent. Dima and Oksana are very hospitable and responsible people. I recommend them to everyone:)

I'm really happy to be hosted by Dmitry. He's tremendous experience in CS. I was shocked to see the book of all his visitors, awesome idea to do!) Hope to see you again and present you a magnet from Brest. Best wishes! ;)

I had the chance to spend 2 nights at Dmitry and Oxana, they are both very nice and extremely welcoming, I am really happy to have met them. Also their place in Minsk is clean and comfortable. Hope to meet them again.

It was really nice staying with Dmirty :) before even meeting us Dmirty suggested that we stay in his home, while he is going away for the New year. It was so sweet, such trusting for leaving their homes for us , I love it, it really gives me the feeling of unity of people all around the world. so we took care of their amazing cat Floyd. :) also, we trained our Russian with his wife Oksana, but Dmirty speaks very good English. so thanks for everything, give kisses to Floyd and welcome to Riga! :)

text: Oksana and Dimitry hosted me for my first 4 days in Minsk. We had some great conversations and they were very helpful although we didnt get to spend much time together because of work. We met again after 2 weeks which was great and I hope we meet again in Lithuania. They are an honest, open, lovely couple and I recommend you stay with them and their panther Floyd :)

I don't even know how to describe this experience... Dmitry and Oksana are wonderful people, their house is full of love and laughs and it made me feel completely welcome. They are kind, helpful and respectful all the time and have nice stories to share. Their cat, Floyd, is one important member of the family and is so cute, so adorable, that I wanna to be around him all the time. 
I really hope they can go to Brazil and enjoy the open borders that we have now :)

Thank you so much for accepting my last minute request :) I stayed with Dmitry two days and we had some interesting conversations about the life in Belorus. Moreover, their cat is so awesome with his own royal character. You are very welcome in Kyiv! :)

We had no chance to know each other better, because I have stayed in their home just one night. But they were very polite when I was very late (after 11 p.m.) and woke them up. They gave me a comfortable bed in cozy separate room. We had some shirt conversations at the kitchen with Dmitry as everyone was sleepy :-) At morning Oksana cooked for me a perfect vegetarian breakfast :-) Very kind guys, hope we will meet again :-)

Absolutely positive guys! Dimitri and Oksana saved me from the cold boring night in Minsk. I had to spend the night in the hostel! but I do not like hostels, u know;)! their house was destroyed by a little)) but there was a lovely cat, sunflower seeds and long conversations in the kitchen. so I visited one more place "must do" in Minsk on Kamennaya Gorka;). Thank you!!!

It was cool to see local home and family life of Minsk from inside. Dmitri and Oksana provided us corner to sleep on the floor and a cup of coffee in the morning.  We were supposed to stay two nights but our Lithuanian friends came to run in Minsk Half Marathon, so we decided that it is most convenient for everyone to stay with them nearby start location and ended up staying only one night. However it was really fun, we went out and had a huuuge (2kg.) pizza, beer tower and good company.  Dmitri and Oksana are hospital people and owns a huge ball of fur (their cat Floyd) which loves to sleep in the sink in the bathroom and could be angry sometimes with new people. Dmitri is really keen in meeting new people from all over the world and have a lovely way of expressing himself in gestures and Oksana is ambitious girl who promised to learn English next time we meet :)

Dima and Oksana accepted my very last minute request and it was awesome!
 I got the chance to meet locals and practice my Russian, we had some food together, beer and interesting conversations about life, cultural differences and some personal stuff as well :)
They both were very friendly, helpful and kind!
I even agreed to keep their tradition and did a photo with Dima))
Totally recommending this great couple!

Dima and Oksana are very friendly, hospitable, kind guys. And they have a very cute cat. A clean and comfortable home)Dima prepares very delicious coffee.This was my first experience on couchsurfing, were only the most positive impressions

Staying with Dmitry and Oksana was a fascinating chance to see into the lives of some super cool Belarussians. Even though sometimes communication was a bit tough, we managed and I had a lot of chance to practice my Russian : ) –õ–æ—à–∞—Ä–∞! Also their cat did not like belly rubs, but that's okay, he gave me some cool scars to show off :P Hope you enjoy the Nutella, and you two are welcome in Paris anytime!

Dmitry is a very friendly and kind guy. He's the one who made our stay in Belarus possible and   we're very grateful to him. Thanks to Dmitry we had unforgettable time in Minsk with a jolly Belarusian-Ukrainian-Polish team of hitchhikers. We hope to see each other again, this time in Poland.
They are friendly family who are very funny, positive and good-hearted people. I spend very good time with them, enjoying part of their food and having played with their tom-cat :)

Dmitry is very friendly and fun. He told me a lot about hitchhiking and gave some good tips. We had nice interesting conversation. 
You definitely need to meet Dmitry! He is an amazing person.

We stay with Dmitry for one day. And after that take a way to home. It was really nice end of our little trip to Belarus. We talked a lot, discussed some interesting case of history, policy and politics. Most of all I remember Dmitry's personal story about his grand-grandpa. Thank you so much for that knowledges!
Also we take a chance to see not central part of capital. And I can conclude that Minsk is very beautiful, cosy, clean and welcoming city at all. By the way, It was very funny excursion around residential district))) Thanks ;))
Individual word deserve Dmitry's cat Floyd. So impressive Baron! I think that nobody can't to be indifferent to this fluffy)))
I glad to know Dmitry. Hope that you with Oksana will take a wonderful time in Saint-Petersburg in short term. 
I wish you good luck in all undertakings! 
With best regards,
Anna

text: What a week I had with Dmitry in Brest! The "simple procedure" of foreigners registration turned out to be a real nightmare!! I don't know how many hours we spent to go through the belarussian bureaucratic maze but it took us three days to get it done... Surely Dmitry's worst CouchSurfing experience ever but still he never lost his smile neither his humor even in the most stressful clock race!! But if we forget about that administration struggle - which has nothing to do with CS - surfing Dmitry's couch has been a great experience! :) He is a kind, generous, open-minded and down-to-earth young man with a good sense of humor and his family is just as amazing as he is!! My russian language skills being unexistant they all did a lot of efforts to exchange a few words in english with me and they made me feel welcomed from the very beginning!! :) So at the end of the day it has been - for me at least and despite all the struggles - a really positive CS experience and to a larger scale a great human experience! Dmitry I don't know to let you know how sorry I am for that bureaucratic mess neither do I know how to tell you how thankful I am for all what you did for me during my time in Brest! If you ever need a hand with some canadian visa application just let me know : I will personally call the Prime Minister to make sure you get you visa granted!! :P

text:
"A good traveler has no fixed plans, and is¬†not¬†intent on arriving." - Lao Tzu¬†

Doesn't matter how long they stayed with me or how much time we spent together. What matters is how lucky I am to host these lovely couple.
Tanya ana Maksim seemed like they were hosting me and I would describe them as generous, curious, funny, full of energy and too many best qualities that came to mind.
They inspired me about interesting things and I've learnt from them a lot. We had a great time full of emotions and fun and my family missing them right now because they are amazing people. We visited many destinations and we've explored new places together.
I don't want to describe their trip in Morocco because I'm afraid to miss something, but you can ask them how was it, they have a lot to tell you.

Maksim and Tanya are no longer guest for me, they are one of my best friends and I'm looking forward to see them again in Morocco or maybe in Belarus or somewhere in this world.

Lots of love, 
Anouar

Tatyana & Maksim were great guests.
They were polite and showed interest to see how an Portuguese family works in a daily life
I especially enjoyed the attention they paid to my kids. With good experiences like, I¬¥m sure my kids will be great couchsurfers when they grow up!
Oh, and the Belarusian pancakes are the best! Thank you!

I hosted Tanya and Maks for a short time and we had a great day going out in cologne, even though the weather was not very nice - but that is normal for cologne in January haha. 
We walked along the Rhine river promenade, up the triangle tower, entered the K√∂lner Dom, and went to a Brauhaus eating and drinking. My girlfriend joined us. Tanya and Maks are very talkative, curious, friendly and have a lot to tell. 
They brought me some sweet local gifts, thanks again, I'm exited to consume them ;). When I came back in my apartment - I had to leave earlier in the morning than they - kitchen and dishes were cleaned and they left me a nice postcard from Belarus :), thank you. 
I wish you both a nice ongoing trip, better weather and hope to see you again. 
Best regards.

Tatyana and Maksim are two lovely guys!!! Kind, polite and talkative... 
I shared good moments with them, cooking together italian and belarusian dishes üòä
I would like to meet them again one day in Minsk and absolutely yes, I would host them again in my home üòä
See you soon Tania & Maksim!!!

Tatyana and Maksim were very nice guests at my place. We had delicious meals together, and talked a lot about both our countries! They're very curious and it was a pleasure to know we also share many common interests. I was a little busy, it was a pity I didn't have the time to hang out during the day, but the evenings made up for that!
I really hope to visit you guys back in Belarus, a mysterious country to me :)
Cheers!

Tania is a very enthusiastic young lady, it is easy to feel she is deeply involved in CS, and this for a long time (she actually had a profile before creating a common one with Maks). Although she sometimes has difficulties with English vocabulary she is very communicative and smiling but when she unhappily was sick. Maks is a way more quiet person, he listen to other people talking and helps Tania for English vocabulary when she misses some words. He trust what his friends say even if they are not native. They came with some nice presents from their country and it was nice from Tania to bring a cake for her birthday (which, weirdly, is the same as my brother's one). I didn't see them that much in fact but when Tania got really sick and I helped to fix the problem but I'm sure they are good hosts.

I hosted Maxim for 1 night and although we didnt spend a lot of time together, he seemed like a friendly and fun person. He was very polite and let us sleep even though he was in Riga for half a day and wanted to see the city. I would definitely host him again and I hope to meet him in Minsk.
Have a good trip Max!
Tanya and Max are a very nice couple, they are very friendly, polite and really interested in sharing time with the other couchsurfers.

We absolutely LOVED Tanya and Max! They were one of the best couchsurfers we have ever hosted. They had, what we call an "eastern soul", full of kindness, hospitality (even though we were supposed to host them, they made us feel like a part of family!!), their profound understanding of life and the world despite their young age, they were just amazing! Guys, we would love to meet you whenever you go, or even better, visit you in your place! See you soon beautiful people, you will be remembered! <3

text: Having hosted Tanya and her boyfriend Maxim as part of their 2-week Euro trip has been an honor.  Considerate, amiable, educated, talkative and very charming, I felt we connected instantly. They resisted 9 hours of intensive walking during which we shared our different views about our cultures, experiences and they had the opportunity to try local food (thumbs up for mandarines! :D). All in all, an amazing experience. If vouches still existed I would have vouched for you!

text:
They are a super nice couple. I have no words to describe how nice they are :-)
I‚Äòm really happy and lucky that they accepted my request and we could spent some time together. They are really friendly! Their hospitality is fabulous!
Maks showed me some good local restaurants, really tasty typical meal. He also showed me a little bit of the City, in a short night-walk, after his work (really gently).
Tanya gave me some hints from places in Minsk and nearby to visit like ‚Äì The Belarusian State Museum of Rural Architecture and Life. She also gave me a little map of the city.
They also arrange an Opera for me at the National Academic Bolshoi Opera and Ballet Theatre. That was also amazing!
In the evening, at their apartment we had some tea together, with a really delicious/superb cookie. Once you eat one, you get instantly addicted and don‚Äôt stop to eat anymore :-P hehehe
Not just the cookies, hehehe, but there are so many reasons that make them really nice persons, good friends! Their hospitality, care with each other, everything wonderful!! TOP! I'm glad that I meet them.
I hope to see you again! Soon or later, somewhere in the world... and be always welcome here in Germany, in Brazil, everywhere!!!
All the best!!
Warm greetings :-)
Emilio

It was a very nice stay in the appartement of Tatyana and Maksim. They are very friendly people who like to communicate. They were also very helpfull and stayed in touch with me when I was travelling in Minsk. The appartement is very clean and in a recent building, in a new developed area of Minsk. Tatyana also made something to eat, and picked me up by car. The couch at night was very comfortable. So... what do I have to say more... I can only recommend everyone to stay with this young couple when you are planning to visit Minsk.

I want to write really much about Max and Tatiana, they are super friendly,helpful,kind and comfortable persons, I felt  like home in theirs clean and cozy apartment with their hospitality , I hope that life will gave me chance to meet them again.

Tatyana and Maks are generous, warm and welcoming hosts. I reached out to them for a few nights visit to Minsk and they have been so hospitable and entertaining. Maks and Tatyana shared their stories of travel and were happy to share their knowledge of the history behind Belarus and introduce me to their cuisine. We visited a Great Britain festival, old town and local tourist spots followed by some bars to round off my first day. The second was spent with friends, fashion markets and visiting graffiti works on Oktyabrskaya St. followed by a meal with Tatyana‚Äôs mom and brother. They are the quintessential hosts and I highly recommend them if you ever visit Belarus. I hope one day to return the hospitality to you both.

I really appreciate that stay witch this nice couple in his house and have the opportunity to taste a good breakfast and excellent lunch witch his company. Thanks to much for assist me to visit the city of Minsk and hope to see you again one day...spasiva

Tatiana and Maks are the nicest couple. They gave us a separate room in their lovely apartament, met us at arrival, showed us the city, party with us, made us delicious breakfast and more. 
We had an awesome time, and can't than them enough for their hospitality and help.

I stayed with Tanya and Maks for 2 days and they are amazing hosts. They are lovely couple and they share their happiness and positive energy with you. They have many funny stories and shared experiences about CS and travelling. 
We discovered the city and a traditional village together, had breakfast, dinner and lunch, had conversation about many things for hours. It was great to spend some time with both of them. They also don't let me get lost in the cyrillic alphabet until I got the correct bus to leave the Minsk. I am soo happy to meet you and wish to see you in my hometown :)
I had a great stay with Tatyana and Maksim. They were both really friendly and I felt very comfortable. They also had one of the best showers I have used on this trip. 10/10 :)

I have stayed 3 nights in these lovely couples' flat and I didn't feel like a guest...I have felt like staying at my home...Their flat is so modern and clean but the most important thing about them is they are absolutely hospitality...Also it was great to hear many stories about their travels and travellers who hosted by them...
Cold weather on the outside was only problem for me while staying with you guys...I hope to meet you again somewhere over the world or in Minsk again...
Thanks for everything; it was a pleasure to meet with you bye:))))

I liked to stay with them, was interesting to talk. We all are busy people but our schedule were the same. They provided me a good  and comfortable place to stay and gave me information about Minsk.  Thank you very much. Cheers

My boyfriend and I cannot thank Tatyana and Maksim enough for everything they did for us. First off, they gave us helpful information about applying for a visa to Belarus, then they hosted us for three nights, extending it an extra night when we couldn't find anyone else to stay with. Then, after we got in a bit of trouble with registration process in Minsk, Tatyana left her office to take us to the immigration office, and didn't return to work in order to stay with us, translating and talking to the police, trying to figure out a way to get us out of trouble, and not get us deported out of Belarus!! We would have been absolutely screwed without her and Maksim, and would have been forced out of the country. She was so good about it, even though we felt terrible for taking her out of work. We also met for tea when Tatyana had the time and they gave us some really helpful information about the town with a map.
They're such a friendly and nice couple with good travel stories and we hope to see them again in the future. 
Thanks again guys!

Tatyana & Maksim were wonderful hosts. For my request Tanya & Max got a positive answer at once. When I arrived in Minsk, we immediately got in touch and met up. It was raining and Tanya brought me an umbrella, a map and gave some advices. She is caring. I stayed with them for two days, it was a relaxing holidays in Minsk. They were too kind to make me dinner and allow myself to relax in their house. Talking with them was a pleasure, they are an amazing couple with a passion for travel.

I  always remember Tanya and Max. They are always my friend and I am sure we will keep in touch  for future. They are exceptional couple.They are  both so friendly,trustable and helpfull people. I spent great time with them. Tanya is a nice cook.Ohhh I will try your recepie Tanya. Thank you for hosting me, thanks for gifts shortly thanks  for memorable moments...
If you come to Minsk you should  know them, strongly recommend.
See you soon in Ankara.

Excellent couple, who brought us to the stadium who hosted us who helped us in everything, seriuos and trustful people.  Wow.
One of my best experiences with CS!

They are friends now and I hope to host or help them while in Belgium.

They DESERVE to be hosted!!!!

Claudio

text:
If you want to fall in love with Belarus, Minsk and its inhabitants, I order you to stay with Tanja, Max and Svetlana. 

They are not only excellent host (beds, sheets, towels, local food and drinks etc...), they are wonderful guides, superheroes ( cf. lost credit card, translations, directions, transportations, schedules etc...) but in top of all, the greatest/kindest/nicest people I ever met on a trip! (probably ever ever....)

They transformed this initial cool trip with friends into an awesome one. A one I will tell the story to my great grand children in 120 years (Yes, I plan to live that long :p) 

You may have to fight them a little to pay the restaurant bill, but DO IT, they deserve way more and will give you back at least a couple hundred times. 

BEWARE, if you are not afraid to let a few tears drop when saying goodbye, you will regret not being hosted there.

And guys, I'm looking forward to see you again very soon! You are welcome anytime, anywhere I am. 

Thanks again. 

Cheers. 

Guillaume.

In the evening by car we drove through the city and she showed us a beautiful night city Minsk! In the evening we watched the movie the Brest fortress and in the morning she called us a taxi. We invited her to visit us and parted very good friends:)
Definitely recommend to stay in Minsk Nastia, and to take her to visit anywhere in the world:)

All in all - great experience we had staying at her place and I definitely recommend Natasha to others either to meet, or host or stay with her and the family :)
It Was my first time being hosted and Natasha is a great host extraordinary soul, marvelous person. It was an amazing experience with your family. Definitely recommend her!
I host Natasha and her family  just one night. That were very cool and good experience.

Natasha, Sergey:

Thank you so very much for everything!

Natasha hosted us for 4 days during the New Year holidays: from 31 December to 3 January. She was kind enough to do so, even though our request was very short notice! 

She drove us from another place where we stayed the previous night to her house, which came in very handy: we had some heavy luggage.

At first, we thought we'd be staying with her and her wonderful family. You can imagine our amazement when we learnt that she was leaving the whole apartment at our disposal, along with her beautiful cat!! That was like a gift from above:  we were all alone in this apartment with a big kitchen (I love kitchens!), keeping an eye on the cat (I love cats!), and seeing the New Year in. Amazing!

Then, when she returned, she arranged for us to stay with her friend for 2 nights, who happened to live in a neighbouring house.

All this is just like Natasha: she is very kind, thoughtful, and attentive. We had some wonderful discussions about our profession and life in general with both Natasha and her husband, Sergey.

I wish we had more time for communication, though. I do hope we meet again, soon! 
Natasha, Sergey, Alyosha: you are most welcome to our place!

I highly recommend staying and hosting them!

Natasha and her family met us so warmly that we felt as we were the members of their family. They provide us sleeping bags, shared  delicious dinner and told interesting stories about their traveling, gave some tips about traveling around Minsk. After your stories my wish to arrange wild trip becomes stronger and I hope to make it real this summer. 

Unfortunately we didn't get to Hatyn so I hope to meet you again) and for sure you are welcome in Moscow
Natasha, Sergey and Lesha are very cool guys!!! I'm  go into raptures!  I hope we see you again!

text: Valery is a super host! I was supposed to arrive on Saturday, but the flight was cancelled so I arrived on Sunday early in the morning at his flat but he welcomed me anyway and provided me with everything I needed! After some hours of sleep we went for a walk and spend some time at october street, a hip and alternative place in Minsk with supernice murials. There was also a small event going on, where local people gathered together to enjoy live. They sold handmade stuff and there were some dancing and self-defense lectors as well. Really nice! Afterwards we went to a bar to attend in a concert- what can I say, Minsk has way more to offer than people might think. And Valery does his best to show you the best sides of the city, he is smart, knowledgeable, caring, decent and really a nice guy, who loves koalas. He even cooked for me. text:

On the first day, Sasha took me on several city guides tours and every evening he acted as the guide : parks, cafes, art zones, etc. One day we went out of town for Sasha's training (yachting) and it was one of the best experiences in my life : to meet the sunset on the bow of the yacht.
Thank you Sasha for the warm welcome, for the good tips of what you can see in Minsk. Thanks to him, I saw Minsk in all its glory and will remember it as one of the most beautiful and hospitable cities

Both are awesome. They stayed at my place for only one night but the whole time was awesome. text:
I have no words to thank Alexander and his mum for having me at their place. I‚Äôve stayed 3 nights at their home but I could have stayed 3 weeks!
They are super helpful, nice human beings, friendly and funny. I had the best time in Minsk and they were a huge part of it.
Their place is close to the city center but his mum drove us around some days. She also made a delicious dinner, and alex picked me up and dropped me of at the train station.
I can‚Äôt thank them enough and I super recommend you to stay with them if you have the chance.
Thank you Alex and Elena for being so kind and friendly to me. I already miss you guys and Lori (their stunning sweet cat!).
Thank you thank you! Xx

Alexander and his mother Elena invit me to visit Minsk, a nice city.
I did spent 4 night with them and their nice sphinx cat & chinchilla.
Elena drove me everywhere in the city and in the parcs.
We enjoyed very nice meals together. Elena did cooked me some very good recepies of her mother. I did made a ceviche and a quiche with lots of problems with molds, oven, ... but at the end, it was delicious.
Alexander took me by night to a nice Jaz concert.
The last day, he did show me a lot of thinks, walking together in the old city.
I show them the "lost Eiffel Tower of Minsk" and "Paul", the famous french bakery, where we could purchase "french baguettes". They didn't knew about these "2 french speciality of Minsk".
So, we were happy to both have shared a lot of things "cultural & food".
Very nice family, that I hope to see in the next future, perhaps in Ecuador ???
Next time, I will try to win you with my game "The little Pigs" !!!
Hope you will find good & cheap accomodations for your next trip.

You will have very good times if you invite them or if you have the pleasure to visit them in Minsk.

Thanks a lot

Michel

Alexander is super welcoming guy!

I stayed in his home for 3 nights. 
His flat is cosy, comfortable and has a lot of stuff (many books, board games and other different interesting things). He arranged me a place for sleep and it was great and comfortable. 
Also he has friendly mom. She told about her traveling and cooked tasty dinner for us. And he has cute cat and chinchilla. 

Alexander knows his city very well and was good guide. He showed me around the city and told some facts about places. 

He took me on Birthday party to hang out with his friends. It was really awesome. Especially the game! I'll remember cucumber for all my life (:D) 

Thank you very much for good weekends! I had so much fun for during my stay. I would recommend Alex!
Sasha is a pretty Nice bit with a lovely mother!

I spent a very good time with Nikita and Lena even if the moment was brief. I was very happy to heard about about their country. They are very polite, well-mannered and they speak a good English. I‚Äôm looking forward to see them in Minsk !

Nikita and Elena spend a night at my place during their tour in France. They are such a nice and easy-going couple, and I felt very comfortable letting them sleep in my apartment. We spend a evening chatting about different topics and discussing their plans for the next day. I wish both of you to enjoy your travel in France, and to enjoy all of your next travels as well !
They are very polite and respectful. They are opened minded and enjoy speaking. I enjoyed having them at home!

I hosted Nikita and her girlfrield for two nights. I had nice discussions with them about life in Finland and Belarus. Nikita had interesting insights about programming with the .Net framework. Nikita is a smart guy. They respected my rules regarding arriving not too late at home. They are friendly people.

I hosted Nikita and his girlfriend Elena for two nights, and they were both super nice! Thery are very friendly and make a lovely couple. They were very active during the day and we saw each other later at my place for dinner&drinks. Nikita was very easy to host as he has already a lot of experiences on CS. Besides, he knows a lot about all kind of interesting subjects, history, languages, travels etc.. Highly recommended guests! :)

Thank you Nikita ;)  You and Lena are really nice and interesting people, it was a pleasure for us to host you! It seemed to be in Belarus for a while.. draniki (a typical belarusian dish) helped a lot ;) Definitely recommended to host this couple!
Hope to come to Minsk some day! ;)

text: I am personally overseeing the construction of Nikitas statue next to Victory Square! Together with his wife Lena, I had the most wonderful stay! They are super easy to talk to, great senses of humor,  very intelligent and Nikita might have the best English in all of Minsk! They even picked me up from the station, introduced me to some Belarussian delacacies, and showed me around town. They always made me feel welcome. Truly this is one of the great Couchsurfing couples in the world! My stay in Minsk would not have been the same without them. More than that though, I think I've made some friends. If you want to see what CS is about, meet them. The question is, when will you come visit me?!

Wow! Wow! Wow! Nikita and Lena are incredible hosts.  If everyone in CS hosted like them, millions more people would be in the CS community.  Let me try to count the ways that they were outstanding hosts: Nikita picked me up from the train station at midnight to take me home; when I arrived a delicious feast was served; the next morning after a delicious breakfast, Nikita took me to change money and then to downtown Minsk where I followed his and Lena's intelligent suggestions of what to see; despite the fact that I came almost an hour late to our meeting place, they waited to take me back to their home; and the next morning they delivered me to the train station.

Besides that they were also great conversationalists, intelligent, warm, insightful, great English speakers, knowledgeable about Belarus society as well as western culture and behaviors. I can continue with the compliments - generous, warm, fun to be with, curious about other people and other societies, and incredibly hospitable. I can not recommend them highly enough.  If in Minsk and you have an opportunity to stay with them, you should definitely ask them to host you.  You will enjoy every minute.

Great host and admirable guy, I really enjoyed the time I spent with him. It was a quite nice experience as I learnt a lot about Finland, Belarus and Europe in general...even he shared great tip and data about Azerbaijan and Indonesia, un genio! He cooked a traditional Belarus dish, recommended me places to visit in Helsinki and other Finnish cities, took me to the Soumenlinna island and finally we went to a delicious Finnish restaurant. Thanks for your time and patience, it was marvelous to meet you, you and your girlfriend are more than welcome in Costa Rica üòä

text: Very knowledgeable and fun guy. Even did my laundry for me when I was running out of time. One of my best stays ever. Pity I made it a little inconvenient for him on the last day by being late to leave due to reasons out of my control but he was super cool about it. He also introduced me to many new things and ignited my interest in mathematics again. Also polished my russian accent :) amazing dude I would definitely stay with him again.

Nikita is a super rich guy - from cultural richness to his outright possession of a wealth of worldly knowledge, he keeps enlightening his surroundings. And from start till end, I found him to be a very open-minded, friendly, reliable, refined, & intellectual young man with absolute positive vibes. He enriched me about Belarus's  major historical events and we also exchanged a lot of knowledge on world politics, books & movies. With an interesting guy like Nikita, you will never get bored and believe me, he has good hands on cooking as well. I feasted on the Belarusian pancakes he prepared for breakfast. Overall, it was a pleasure staying at Nikita's place & I look forward to host him & his GF in Mauritius, so I can reciprocate his kindness and warm hospitality. üòä

Nikita taught me a lot about Belarus and the culture there! And he cooked me wonderful potato pancakes! I really can't find the words to describe how good they tasted. If you're looking for a host who's going to want to hang out the entire time, I doubt he'll be the man for you, but if you prefer a more hands-off host, he'll be perfect. He does live about 30-35 minutes from the city center also, which is good to know! Overall I had a positive experience

The best part of Nikita's home is all the free champagne and caviar you can pick to your stomach's fill. The only lacking part was the missing seven servants. Unfortunately they were all on a holiday. I can't believe this is what I get for free. Next time I will charge 10 euros.

Nikita, thanks a lot for hosting me! This was my first couchsurfing experience and I'm truly glad that I have discovered such an interesting way to travel :)

text:

Even if he didn't have time during the day, we managed to have long conversations about many topics as he's a very interesting, easygoing and open minded guy.

He helped us to understand the product labels at the supermarket...and dared to let us cook one of our speciallities ;)

Much more than expected... and of course he -together with other new friends we met in Belarus thanks to Couchsurfing- taught us what the "Hospitality" term means.

I strongly recommend to host Nikita and/or to meet him if you have the opportunity, as he's a great and interesting person to share time with.

text:
Vitaly & Anna were one of the best couples I met on couchsurfing and reminded me how great couchsurfing in meeting great people...

I arrived Minsk at night and didnt get to see the city properly yet, but I already fell in love with Minsk because of them. They welcomed me to their home, cooked me a delicious Belarusian dish and let me stay at their cozy home for two nights! They are respectful, kind, wonderful and smart people that made our conversations felt like never ending... we just love to exchange stories and time wasn't on our side, as they had to work on the weekdays...

Not to forget their best friend Kolas - that came to join us from the first night. He was simply awesome because he just had the free time to show me most of his great city - Minsk! Thank you man, I really appreciate it!

Thank you guys! 
You are a great example of how beautiful people can be... I feel our friendship will be long lasting and I believe we will meet again someday somewhere... 

... and for those who are reading this! You wont regret meeting or hosting them... and they have  a wish to show their well behaved toddler the world too - so, if you love wonderful families, you will not regret them!...

I cannot say enough about my experience with Oskar and Natasha. The actual home was nice and welcoming, clean, cozy and easy to navigate, I even had my own room and bed, but that is nothing compared to their company. 

When I arrived Oskar was at work but Natasha greeted me and shared wine, and meal, and nice conversation. The next day, Oskar came home with tons of fresh local veggies from his father's farm and we all cooked a lovely vegetarian dinner together. Oskar took me to the Khatyn Memorial, a tribute to almost three million Belarusians who died during World War 2. It was an emotional and educating experience. We all had some great cocktails at Oskar's bar. He is a great cook and bartender. 

I had a wonderful experience with the two of them and it definitely made my trip to Minsk more memorable. I hope to meet the two of them traveling in Asia. If you have the chance to Meet, Host, and Surf with Oskar and Natasha, you should take it!

text:
Misha and Olga were perfect host with tons of energy and eager to learn about different cultures/languages. They picked me up from the airport and immediately gave me a tour of the city by showing me monuments and their ever famous diamond shaped library. Soon after they took me to a soviet style grocery store where purchased items for my first Belarusian meal of mushroom and potato dumplings. That same night they showed me how to get to the city center but taking the tram and metro with me and showing me how to buy transportation tickets.

Every night during my 3 day stay was filled with laughter and inquisitive questions. I throughly enjoyed my stay with them and hope to see them soon. They are very friendly and hospitable. On my last day Misha went out of his way to make sure that I got on the right train to Brest.  Misha is quite a handy man so if you have any broken electronics give it to him to fix. There‚Äôs never a dull moment with this awesome couple. 

Peace, 
Martene

text:

Yulia hosted me for 3 out of 5 nights that I spent in Belarus in Aug 2018. It was a bit funny trying to find her place, since I wasn‚Äôt used to the apartment numbering system that they use in this part of the world, I went to 3 different floors of her building before finally going to the right one! LOL proves that you travel to experience different quirks around the world. :)
Her apartment is well-located and comfortable, it‚Äôs possible to walk from the train station if you don‚Äôt have much luggage. I had the honour of trying her homemade babka, and she discovered that I really love potatoes and smetana. :) Good for living in Belarus!
She was mostly busy with work for most of the time, but patiently helped me with my various questions about getting around the city, and took the time off to eat dinner out together twice, and surprisingly we went to a restaurant that‚Äôs quite near her place but which she never went to before.
Thank you for hosting me Yulia, I hope to see you again someday! Maybe a shopping trip in China? ;)

Yulia met me and my husband very friendly! She is a very sweet and active girl. She showed us about interesting places in Minsk, and we had wonderful trip to the local psychedelic zoo together)))) 
She's very intelligent and kind young woman with positive vibes and big plans to discover the world and meet new people. We wish you the best of luck in everything you decide to do!

We started laughing loudly on the elevator, cause they were so funny and spontaneous, as if we know each other since ages...they came on the worst period, cause I've been sick, but it wasn't that bad though ! It ruined an experience that could have been one of the best ever, but it has shown me, how human and caring they were ! They were meant to stay 4 nights, but after two nights, where i was struggling with sickness, I standed up the next day at midday, and the surprise is : I have found food made, the house cleaned and their luggage prepared ! They booked in a hotel to let me some space, and to let me recover...they didn't know how much their presence were valuable, i was a bit mad at them inside, cause they decided alone, but i was happy at the same time for meeting up with such people.

Thanks for everything = )

text:
My experience with him and his friends wasn't negative but I wouldn't host them again. Mikita came to my flat with 3 of his friends, they stayed from Friday till Sunday morning. I went out with them to get couple of drinks on Friday evening  and we had breakfast and lunch together on Saturday. I took them to Schindler's factory and there we've split because I had some stuff to do at my flat. They had a bus back to Minsk at 4:30 am and they came back from the center around 2am. I thought they will pack their stuff and leave, instead they were drinking vodka in my kitchen and woke me up twice around 3 am. They woke me up again when they were leaving. 

Another thing is that all surfers that stayed at my place wanted to help out with cleaning, shopping or dishes at least. I started to think that this is a standard but maybe Mikita and his friends had different view on that. This is the first time I felt like a hostel owner. Well, this is only my opinion, other hosts liked Mikita so maybe you'll have better luck than me hosting him.

Time dashed past and I was only sorry that I wasn't on this occasion able to host him and Pavel. Next time he's in London hopefully that will be put right.

hey folks!¬†Let me speak from my heart! üòã
I stayed for 1 night at Valentine‚Äôs place and I had a great CS experience with him during 2 days. We walked a lot!  So I had great opportunity to expand knowledge about Minsk and about life in Belarus. He is passionate about architecture and Minsk. He developed a plan to see major city-sights in short time. Thanks for that! 
Over walks&conversations with this intelligent person definitely widen my horizons and made me want to come back for longer chats.¬†He presented me another Minsk, seriously I thought that Minsk is the city without youngsters‚Äô energy and nightlife. I liked Minsk so much and I will definitely come back. 
Valentine is very friendly and polite person. He really cares about his surfers and always offers them the best. I slept on his bed with a nice and warm blanket and clean linens. 
Moreover Valentine has adorable cat. They‚Äôre in love. You will feel it. üòâ
If you have an opportunity - do meet Valentine! I highly recommend him as a host or surfer (!) 
I'm sorry that we had not so much time together. Hope to see you soon again!¬†
Cheers!

I want to write a GRE essay to describe this less-than-48h trip. It‚Äôs really kind of Valentine that he gave me his bedroom and became a real ‚Äúcouchsurfer‚Äùhimself. Minsk has come alive in such a fascinating dusk because of Valentine‚Äôs knowledge about all the histories and the mix of European and communist aesthetics behind it, the city and my host are unbelievably amazing, that I cried about 10mins because of accidentally losing a roll of film taken there, precisely like ripping out my heart. 

I don‚Äôt know a lot before about post rock music except famous artists like King Crimson, but I would love to discover this filed further and further after listening the works of Valentine‚Äôs band, it‚Äôs so alternative with abundant delicate details, you can‚Äôt resist it.

Even when Valentine was busy, he introduced me to his energetic and lovely friend, we also spent a good time together. Are Belorussian people all angles?

P.S. Phoebe is so sweet, I already missed that little cute alien!

Ok, I have to be honest: I am disappointed by Couchsurfing that allows me to say "positive" and not more. Probably "awesome" would be a better word to summarize my experience with Yuliya.
She is so far the best guest I have ever met and I think it will be very hard for others to move her from the top of this "chart" of my own.
She is very polite, smart and always in a good mood (her smile can be contagious!); moreover she has many interesting stories and experiences to share. We had very good moments together eating typical Italian food, tasting wine from Tuscany and going out to see the marvelous architecture and city landscapes of Florence. And, of course, we have also had many occasions to laugh!
Be careful: it's almost impossible to avoid falling in love with her, you should trust me about this :)
Yuliya, thanks so much for the time spent together. As I told you, "we cannot foresee our future but we can put us in a positive mood to attract good things"; as you told me, "the main thing is to want to do something". That's why, merging our philosophies, I hope to have soon the opportunity to meet again: in my Italy, in your Belarus or probably in another place of this amazing world.
May all your dreams come true: you deserve it.
Ciao,

Mirko

I was hosted by Yuliya during my first night in Minsk where I came this autumn to attend in a volunteer workcamp. I feel so blessed by meeting this amazing person. When I saw Yuliya's profile for a first time I had this warm feeling that she is a special person and my possible stay with her might be an extraordinary experience. And I wasn't wrong at all!

First of all Yuliya is very caring person who is interested only in having honest and deep relations with people. During our evening and morning talks we were speaking a lot about our feelings, emotions, good and bad life experiences and about our inner worlds. Not with everyone you can have such a conversations! I was and still I am very touched by this. I discovered that we're very similar to each other and I've started to think that we're twin souls from two neighbouring countries. I hope for the future we can make this friendship growing =).

Yuliya is pure kindness. She picked me up from the station and helped me to arrange the meeting with organizers with my workcamp (actually she did it all). She arranged fro us the meeting with her friend Alena and we went to the wonderful cafe with the view to the "city gate of Minsk" I was amazed by. And as a cherry of the top of a cake she prepared a delicious vegan pumpkin pancakes for our breakfast. Dear Yuliya, I appreciate all You have done to me and I can't wait you visit me in Poland. I miss You already very much. You are surely one of the best people I have ever met. Please, keep dreaming and keep growing. Keep discovering yourself in this big and fascinating world. I hope that we can make this trip to Ireland we were speaking about come true =)!

Warm hugs from cold Poland!

Martina Tramp, autumn 2015

She put a lot of effort and thought into what we should see and do together but was still easy going and flexible enough to make things suit both of our moods.

She admitted to being nervous to host for the first time and making sure she was 'doing enough' for her guest. She really had nothing to worry about; she went above and beyond :) 
Thank you for such a fantastic first couchsurfing experience Sasha! I hope we will cross paths again :)

text: Staying with Sergej was one of the best CS experience I have ever had! He kindly invited me to spend Easter with his family in his hometown and it was such a rich experience. Sergei is a truly visionary person with plenty of innovative project ideas, and generally an interesting view on life. He is also very laid-back and a great company to spend time with. His parents were very sweet and communicative, I am much grateful for their hospitality. Sergej, thank you very much, hope to see you again and that time hope to get to know Julia as well!

Sergej was so nice to welcome me at his place in short notice within 1 days. I confess finding my way was a little bit complicated, but he was so nice to pick me up when I was lost.
Sergej lives a bit far outskirts of the city, but when you sleep at night you hear nothing but silence.
He lives in a clean flat with his sister, 2 cars and one dog.
I felt very welcome, and Sergej knew a lot of things about the city.
How to reach the places with the bus or by metro. 
Talking about it.
When you take bus 27 from the back side of the railway station you need about 30 minutes to reach the bus stop. 
From there you walk about 0.7 miles or 10 minutes straight to his place. 
If you prefer the metro it about 30 minutes on foot from piatrouscyna station.
A big mall is not far from there. 
Sergei has trusted me a lot by leaving me his keys while he went away for about 4 days in his flat.
The fridge was stuffed with delicious, self-made food and even has an unstoppable stock of tea. 
I would always come to his place again.
Thank you.

Sergej provided us a friendly welcome. He waited for our arrival at the train station, showed us nice places to go. He is a very interested and curious person and totally fit the CSing spirit. He took time to explain us the meaning of buildings or monuments in the streets which we couldn't understand.
Besides, he loves to host people and he cooked local food for us. It's a shame we didn't have more time to get to know each other better. Wish you the best for your travels around the world!
Unfortunately Julia was not there.

text:
Kiril Levkov! Great man! Can I finish with that?  Apparently not! 
Kiril is a globetrotter! A free-thinker! A workaholic! And a even bigger partyholic! :D :D He walks about like an inquisitive child, always hungry for more. Learning from his inquisitiveness and teaching others from it! He's like Timothy Olyphant from the Hitman movie. He's notices thing which are oblivious to us common folks. Like the dangerously *cough*illegal*cough* extensions of the Soviet era apartment or say the placement of a Gas valve next to combustible materials. I wouldn't be surprised if he went on to build a "Time Machine!!!" This guy is that good!
It's a pleasure to stroll the city with him. Even if you had walked down a alley a thousand times, I bet he'd notice something you have not before.
So, I say to all you folks who are thinking of hosting him; Don't think! Open up your doors, cuz you're in for "The Amazing Kiril experience!"

With loads of love.  You made me wiser and intellectually richer. 
Umar

text:
It was a wonderful experience to be hosted by Artsiom! He is a very nice and talented guy.
He went to the train station to pick me up and showed me around the neighbourhood. It was great having a tea together at his apartment while he was playing some of his music. If you meet him you definitely should ask him to play some of his songs!
The next day we went to France on foot which I enjoyed a lot.
I'm definitely looking forward to hostting Artsiom at my place at some point of the year :-)
Cheers!

Artsiom is an amazing host! He is very thoughtful and accommodating. I enjoyed staying at his place, walking and talking around the new area, and our shared hobby of guitar! He's really talented, and a much better singer/songwriter than I am.
Glad we met, and we'll be meeting again, hopefully soon, in Saarbr√ºcken!

I've met Karol when I started a Europe trip with my friend Martin in Verona.
It was easy to get along with him and his very nice friends, all of them were very welcoming, helpful and truly kind people. 
After a night drinking and celebrating (from which I don't remeber too much, probably because of the very cheap wine OR the wodka-with-salt-and-polish-sausage session- Don't try it! It's dangerous!! :D) we could take a shower there and later they joined us on our ride to Venice :)

Even if we just spend one night in Verona I experienced Karol as a very friendly and open-minded person; it was fun to have him around and I wish him a lot of great travel experiences and joy in his life :)

I met Karol at the lake of Garda, when we both surfed at Riccardos couch. We got along very good, so I visited him one week later, when I came to Verona (where he just moved in). We hat two very cool parties with his friends there, got drunk together and I had so much fun with all of them. Even he couldn't offer me a bed (that was no problem - I could sleep in my van) I could take a shower there, wash my clothes and get some water. Karol is a really friendly person and if you have the chance to meet him - use it! You will have a great time, like I had. 
Karol you are welcome in Germany all the time and I really hope to meet you again.

Katya and Illya were just amazing, such friendly hosts who were remarkably generous with their time, home and company.

They were kind enough to meet me at the bus station, give me their bedroom as they slept on the floor of Katya's sister bedroom(!) and took me on an awesome road trip to see some castles.

We had the pleasure to host Ivan and his girlfriend for two nights in Stockholm and it was a delight from the start. During their stay we had many nice conversations about many different things, and it was clear that Ivan is a guy who likes to search for new things. Ivan is polite, kind, friendly and helpful, a very easy person to host :)

Ivan and Darina are a very sweet couple, thoughtful and with good humor. We shared the same experiences having worked in restaurants, and I particularly enjoyed having them as guests, as they were open, yet respectful and used to having guests themselves. They spoke of their experiences in the Nordic countries, and their future goals. I so hope you make it! That I get to see the two of you again, hiking in Norway or across the water in kayaks. 
Have a great trip home, and all the luck to you in the future!

Ivan and Daryna were great guests! Extremely kind, clean and generous. We had the opportunity to go out together, have dinner and share some nice time together and have nice conversations. I'd host them again at anytime.

text: Ivan was working a lot while I was in Minsk, and I was pretty busy myself. What I can tell from the time that I got to spend with him is that he is a really nice, curious and funny guy to be around. Ivan is a great guy. He is easy to talk to and really smart as well. His English is great (even when you say it isn't). We had some nice conversations and eat some tasty local food. Thanks for everything Ivan and Darina:)!

Although my dates went so crazy because I hitchiked around Ukraine before arrival to Minsk , he was really respectful and hosted me for one night( early morning :) ) , he is a great guy , had a good conversation , they cooked for me , was very friendly and he understood about my crazy and flexible timetable for my travel , thank you a lot.

I spent two unforgettable days with Ivan and Darina in Minsk,  super amazing and interesting couple, we had a lot of interesting life and travel talks, they shared a lot of stories about their adventures in many countries. 
The flat is just awesome, very cozy with great location and a lot of positive energy :)
Minsk is so wonderful with couchsurfers like you ;) 
Wish you a great 2018 year and hope to meet you again.

I really liked staying with a Vanja and Darina. Those both are pretty awesome and I learned a lot about life and living in Belarus. They made me feel welcomed at their place and had no problem that I came home  late sometimes.

Dear Ivan and Darina... You are both such wonderful and thought-provoking persons. I'm so happy to be hosted by you. True spirit of Belarus hospitality. Thank you so much for the most delicious buckwheat with mushrooms I've ever eaten. 
Darina accompanied me for walking around old town and unbelievably beautiful street art quartier. I kindly suggest visit this street Oktyabrskaya to everyone. 
You are the best hosts. 
Hope to see you again one day.
You are always welcome in St.Petersburg and Kareljia. 
Hugs.

text: Sergei hosted me for one night in Minsk during my short stay in Belarus in January 2011. It would really be a pleasure for me to host him someday in Belgrade.

text: Sasha and his brother Denis were my guests while in Milan to attend a trade fair looking for business partners for their company. Great guests, neat and attentive, they know how to cook excellent pancakes, and have a remarkable knowledge of history. Also, without them I would still not know that there is a BIG equestrial monument to Napoleon III in Milan - I thought they were talking about Napoleon I (his statue is rather close to the other one). Come again! There is still a lot about Milan you need to show me! And one day I might take you up on your offer to show me the giant antenna of the submarine communications station in Belarus! :-)

Although I didn't get to spend too much time with Sasha as he was working, he joined me for one evening with two of his other friends that he met the day earlier. He showed me some sights that I would not have seen such as the old factory that's been brought back to life through street art. Hes a calm and friendly guys who wants to spend time with you if he can. In his house I stayed with this mom who always greeted me with a smile and was always feeding me. She's extremely kind and open, when I was leaving their hone she was waving to me from their apartment of window - it felt like she was my own Belarusian mother

Sasha is a very hospitable, cheerful young man. We arrived in Minsk late at night and he kindly offered to meet us. He gave us a separate room, and in the morning he fed the most delicious oat porridge, which I had only to try. Before work, he made a short tour of the city, made a list of places worth visiting. He was always in touch and offered to stay for a few more days. Sasha is a very interesting and versatile person. I'm sure that he will never be bored with him. I am very glad to meet you. We will definitely come again. And we will be happy to host you in Yaroslavl.

Thank you very much for surf Sasha, I am deeply impressed by your hospitality. Very interesting, positive kind person. I wish that in your travels you easily find new interesting people like you. Thank you very much for your help, support, excursion around the city. You are very cool menüòâ

Maks was the amazing guest! During his stay we felt Max like a brother was visitung us. He is very friendly and polite. He can do wonderful things because of his circus experience. Added to that he keeps superior silence and tidy at the place. Thank you Max, you are always welcome again.

Sadly didn't have a lot of time to hang out with Maxim, but I was happy to meet such an interesting person and a kind and friendly guest ! It was pleasure to host him and I hope to meet up in the nearest future in Minsk!

Maksim is just amazing! I hosted him for some days in Moscow. He is a very good, interesting and kind person and an accurate and polite guest. It was so easy to host him that time flew by very fast, wish he stayed longer.;)

text:
Very pleasant guest!
Polite, friendly and easy to interract!

Dasha was my guardian angel in Minsk.  I am extremely lucky to meet her. She was very helpful and  people like her make couchsurfing cool and enjoyable.

She not only hosted me but was also very generous with her time (of course after work). She also prepared breakfasts for me. Basically she provides 5 star service. 

She lives close to the city center, together with her roommate (who i have not seen, she was gone during my stay) and a cat. Generally i am not a pet lover but the whole experience was so good that eventually i ended up liking even Tomatik (dasha's cat). 

Dasha also introduced me to real rhythm of jazz and she also inspired me to do a very exitic trip in cinque terre.
